Ich wollte mich noch mal für eure prompte Hilfe zu meinem Notruf gestern Abend bedanken und euch mitteilen dass ich inzwischen Hilfe gefunden habe was eine Unterkunft für mich und mein Klavier angeht.

Diese indirekte Unterstützung via Geld wäre also eher eine Gemeinschaftsunterstützug zur Lösung meiner Situation.

Vielen Dank, ihr seid eine wirklich tolle Gruppe und ich bin nach wie vor sprachlos über diese Nächstenliebe!

French Foreign Ministry considered unacceptable the statements of Azerbaijan about French presidential candidate Valérie Pécresse after her trip to Nagorno Karabakh, Jean-Yves Le Drian said, answering the questions of MPs in the National Assembly. 

"Aliyev's statements are unacceptable in both form and substance, which I informed the Azerbaijani ambassador in France. 

If I may make a point, I regret that the authorities of the [French] republic hadn’t received any official information about this visit. This is neither appropriate nor superfluous because it is more suitable, in the event of a trip to Stepanakert, to notify the authorities of the republic, who remain at the service of all elected officials.

That said, beyond this incident, it is important that France be in solidarity with Armenia, and we have been..."

In response, Eric Ciotti, the deputy of the Republicans who asked the question, said that candidate Valérie Pécresse is not going to ask Macron's candidate for permission to travel.
